Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_instance_power(25.10)                      report_instance_power(25.10)

Name
       report_instance_power - Generates a text based report for the specified
       instance

Syntax
        report_instance_power

       [-help] <instance> [-file <filename>] [-inst_file <filename>]

       Generates  a text based report for the specified instance. This command
       enables you to determine how the different components of  static  power
       are  calculated.  You  can use the report to debug static power numbers
       after performing power analysis (report_power).

       This command is available through both the static and dynamic power en-
       gines. This command is supported in the dynamic power engine by includ-
       ing this  command  in  the  power  include  file  through  the  command
       set_power_include_file.

       Note:  For dynamic power engine, the report_instance_power command does
       not generate text reports incrementally. If the dynamic  run  has  been
       performed and you need the debug information for a static power number,
       you should re-run power analysis.

       The  report_instance_power  command is not supported in the event-based
       power analysis flow.

Parameters
       -file <filename>
              Writes out the static power analysis report into the  file  that
              you specify.

       -help  Outputs the command usage and a brief description about the com-
              mand parameters.

       <instance>
              Specifies the instances to include in the instance power report.

       -inst_file <filename>
              Specifies  a file that includes a list of instances. The parame-
              ter allows you to report and debug power  numbers  for  multiple
              instances.

              A sample file is given below:

              INST1

              INST2

              INST3

Example
              * The  following command specifies an instance power report file
                debug.rep for the instance top/i_1:

                report_instance_power -file debug.rep top/i_1

Related Information
